docs.abstract: A lack of moral imagination can make deeply ethical actions seem like crimes.
docs.snippet: A lack of moral imagination can make deeply ethical actions seem like crimes.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.’s “Letter From Birmingham Jail” was written as a response to a group of “white moderate” clergy members who claimed to be supportive of the civil rights movement — but who had also called Dr. King’s activism both “unwise and untimely.” For these moderates, civil rights activists were not courageous adversaries of a horribly unjust society, but lawless “outside agitators” threatening the tranquillity of the status quo. And so, rather than commending these activists, they condemned them and blamed the outbreak of violence on their resistance to Jim Crow rather than on Jim Crow itself.

headline.main: Are You a Moderate? Think Again

docs.abstract: When he goes low, Democrats are supposed to go high. Except, it turns out, going low feels wonderful.
docs.snippet: When he goes low, Democrats are supposed to go high. Except, it turns out, going low feels wonderful.
docs.lead_paragraph: Most weeks my Mondays unfold in a well-practiced routine: brush teeth, wash face, walk dog. This morning, I added a new step: spend 15 minutes scrolling through Twitter to see whether anyone had synced that delicious footage of President Trump’s face falling on Sunday — as the World Series crowd is booing him — with the R.E.M. song “Everybody Hurts.”

headline.main: Why Did It Feel So Good to See Trump Booed?
headline.print_headline: Trump  Got Booed.  Can I Smile?

docs.abstract: The deputy was awarded a medal of valor after she shot and killed a man outside a Walmart in 2017.
docs.snippet: The deputy was awarded a medal of valor after she shot and killed a man outside a Walmart in 2017.
docs.lead_paragraph: When a Missouri deputy said she fatally shot a man in 2017 because he was reaching for her Taser, the sheriff’s department awarded her a medal of valor. But after the deputy used the same defense for shooting a woman in the back in August, the county prosecutor pressed charges last week and promised to look into the 2017 shooting again.

headline.main: Prosecutors Re-examine Killing After Missouri Deputy Is Charged in Another Shooting
headline.print_headline: Charges Against Deputy Spur 2nd Look at a Killing

docs.abstract: Experiencing Jeremy O. Harris’s provocative Broadway debut feels fraught, but invigorating.
docs.snippet: Experiencing Jeremy O. Harris’s provocative Broadway debut feels fraught, but invigorating.
docs.lead_paragraph: One evening last month, the John Golden Theatre in Times Square — once the Broadway home for “Avenue Q” and, more recently, “A Doll’s House Part 2” — looked as though it had been transformed into Harlem’s Magic Johnson Theater. Or that’s the way at least one attendee described it, observing the near-full house made up almost entirely of black audience members, who were still humming over the astounding performance we had just witnessed.

headline.main: What It’s Like to See ‘Slave Play’ as a Black Person
